parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Back Failure in Rear-End Collisions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat back to remain upright during a rear-end collision can cause serious injuries to the driver and passengers, including concussions, neck pain, and back injuries.
symptoms: The seat back reclines completely upon impact
pinning or trapping occupants
causing injuries to the neck and back.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to securely mount a child seat in the vehicle can increase the risk of injury or death to the child in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The child seat does not fit safely into the vehicle
according to fire and police department assessments.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belts to retract can cause the belts to remain loose, leaving the driver and passengers unprotected in the event of an accident, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belts do not retract
the seat belts take an excessive amount of time to retract
the seat belts hang up when trying to put them on
the seat belts lock while driving
the seat belts do not move when trying to adjust them
a clicking noise is heard when unfastening the seat belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle fishtails or loses control
the rear of the vehicle slides or swings from side to side
the vehicle is unresponsive to braking efforts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure (De-Beading) and Loss of Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The tire de-beads
the vehicle fishtails or loses control
the rear of the vehicle slides or swings from side to side
the vehicle is unresponsive to steering efforts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag fails to deploy in a crash
the vehicle occupants suffer injuries or fatalities that could have been prevented or mitigated by airbag deployment.
